cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.AI, cs.SI

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The paper proposes an extension to a neural network based associative memory model and analyzes its performance in different scenarios. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper deals with improving the retrieval rate and robustness of a machine learning model in the presence of corrupt messages. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses different error scenarios and proposes approaches to deal with them, which involves concepts from information theory. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes an improvement to an AI model and evaluates its performance in different scenarios. 
5. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper deals with a network model and its performance in different scenarios, which can be relevant to social and information networks.
